abstract: >-
  OpenEtruscan is an open-source platform for Etruscan epigraphy. It
  unifies the inscriptions into one corpus of 6,633 records (the cleaned
  public dataset is a 6,567-row subset), publishes them as Linked Open
  Data, and ships a multilingual encoder (LaBSE + XLM-R with Etruscan-side
  LoRA) that embeds Etruscan and Latin in a shared vector space. It also
  includes a frozen benchmark, rosetta-eval-v1, with random, Levenshtein,
  and model baselines, and instructions to reproduce it.
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-05-24"
